71: /**
72:  * The OffsetMetadataManager manages the offsets of all the groups. It basically maintains
73:  * a mapping from group id to topic-partition to offset. This class has two kinds of methods:
74:  * 1) The request handlers which handle the requests and generate a response and records to
75:  *    mutate the hard state. Those records will be written by the runtime and applied to the
76:  *    hard state via the replay methods.
77:  * 2) The replay methods which apply records to the hard state. Those are used in the request
78:  *    handling as well as during the initial loading of the records from the partitions.
79:  */
